Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if
necessary. Halve, peel, and finely dice @onion{1/2}.

Place potatoes in a large #pot with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches.
Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup potato
cooking liquid, then drain.

Return potatoes to pot. Add @sour cream{3%tablespoon} and 2 TBSP
@butter{1%tablespoon}; mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth and creamy,
adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Taste and season
with @salt{1%tsp} and @black pepper{1%tsp} if desired. Cover and set aside
until ready to serve.

While potatoes cook, toss green beans on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of
@cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper.
Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Cover with #foil to keep warm until ready to serve.

Pat @chicken cutlets{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; place between two
large pieces of #plastic wrap{}. Pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{} until
chicken is about ½ inch thick. Season all over with half the
@dried rosemary{1/2%teaspoon}, remaining garlic powder, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook
until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{} and cover with #foil to keep warm. Wipe
out pan and let cool slightly.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in pan used for chicken over medium-low heat. Add
diced onion; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Sprinkle onion with @flour{1%tablespoon}; stir until coated. Whisk in ½ cup
water and @beef stock concentrate{1}. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring
occasionally, until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: If gravy seems too thick, stir in another splash of water.

Divide chicken, mashed potatoes, and green beans between plates. Spoon onion
gravy over chicken and mashed potatoes. Serve.